How to create virtual enviroment
1. Install Python 3.11
If not installed:
	•	Download from Python official website
	•	During install, ✅ tick “Add to PATH”
2. Open VS Code Terminal

 Open Visual Studio Code
 Then open terminal:
 3. Create virtual environment (venv311)

 "python3.11 -m venv venv311"
 or 
 "python -m venv venv311"
4. Activate virtual environment
on windows: "venv311\Scripts\activate"
on mac/linux: "source venv311/bin/activate"
5. Install packages inside venv
"pip install numpy"

 Pro Tip
" source venv311/bin/activate"
